---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { Shield, Bluetooth, Smartphone, MapPin, Mail, HardDrive } from 'lucide-react';
---

<Layout title="Privacy Policy - Klikkr App">
  <main class="min-h-screen bg-zinc-950 text-zinc-50 font-sans p-6 md:p-12 lg:p-24 selection:bg-emerald-500/30">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto space-y-12">
      
      {/* Header */}
      <div class="space-y-6 pb-12 border-b border-zinc-800/50">
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center text-zinc-400 hover:text-emerald-400 transition-colors text-sm font-medium group">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="mr-2 group-hover:-translate-x-1 transition-transform"><path d="m15 18-6-6 6-6"/></svg>
          Back to klikkr.ch
        </a>
        <div>
          <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-extrabold tracking-tight mb-4">Privacy Policy</h1>
          <p class="text-xl text-zinc-400 font-medium">Klikkr Pro Companion App (Android & iOS)</p>
        </div>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-4 text-sm text-zinc-500 bg-zinc-900/50 p-4 rounded-xl border border-zinc-800/50">
          <span class="flex items-center gap-2"><Shield size={16} class="text-emerald-500" /> Effective Date: {new Date().toLocaleDateString('en-US', { month: 'long', day: 'numeric', year: 'numeric' })}</span>
          <span class="hidden sm:inline">•</span>
          <a href="mailto:support@klikkr.ch" class="flex items-center gap-2 hover:text-emerald-400 transition-colors"><Mail size={16} /> support@klikkr.ch</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      {/* Content */}
      <div class="space-y-12">
        
        <section class="space-y-4">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <div class="p-2 bg-emerald-500/10 rounded-lg"><Shield class="text-emerald-500" size={24} /></div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-zinc-50">1. Core Principle</h2>
          </div>
          <p class="text-zinc-300 leading-relaxed text-lg">
            Our app is designed with a privacy-first approach. The Klikkr Pro app 
            <strong class="text-emerald-400"> does not collect, transmit, or store any personal data</strong> on external servers. 
            There are no user accounts, no cloud sync, and no tracking analytics.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-4">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <div class="p-2 bg-blue-500/10 rounded-lg"><HardDrive class="text-blue-500" size={24} /></div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-zinc-50">2. Local Storage Only</h2>
          </div>
          <p class="text-zinc-300 leading-relaxed">
            All your match data, scores, settings, and paired wristbands are stored <strong>strictly locally</strong> on your own device. When you uninstall the app, all associated data is permanently erased.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-4">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-zinc-50 pt-4">3. Required Permissions</h2>
          <p class="text-zinc-400 mb-6">To function properly as a remote display for your Klikkr Pro wristbands, the app requires specific device permissions.</p>
          
          <div class="grid gap-6">
            <div class="bg-zinc-900/50 border border-zinc-800/50 p-6 rounded-2xl">
              <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
                <div class="p-3 bg-indigo-500/10 rounded-xl mt-1"><Bluetooth class="text-indigo-400" size={24} /></div>
                <div>
                  <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-zinc-100 mb-2">Bluetooth (BLE)</h3>
                  <p class="text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed">
                    This permission is absolutely critical for the app to work. It allows your phone to discover, connect to, and exchange score data with the Klikkr Pro hardware beacons via Bluetooth Low Energy.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-zinc-900/50 border border-zinc-800/50 p-6 rounded-2xl">
              <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
                <div class="p-3 bg-amber-500/10 rounded-xl mt-1"><MapPin class="text-amber-400" size={24} /></div>
                <div>
                  <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-zinc-100 mb-2">Location (Android 11 and older)</h3>
                  <p class="text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed">
                    Due to underlying Android system architecture on older versions, scanning for nearby Bluetooth devices requires "Fine Location" permission. 
                    <span class="block mt-2 text-zinc-300 font-medium">We do not track, determine, read, or share your physical location at any time.</span>
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-4 pt-8 border-t border-zinc-800/50">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <div class="p-2 bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg"><Smartphone class="text-zinc-300" size={24} /></div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-zinc-50">4. Third-Party Services</h2>
          </div>
          <p class="text-zinc-300 leading-relaxed">
            The Klikkr Pro Companion App does not integrate any third-party ad networks, telemetry trackers, or crash reporting services. Your usage remains entirely private.
          </p>
        </section>
        
      </div>

    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>
